# Cloudflare Pages redirects
# Syntax: <source> <destination> <status>
# Docs: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Canonicalise www.esrf.net -> esrf.net (permanent, path + query preserved).
# Cloudflare's "Always Use HTTPS" rule still upgrades http://esrf.net/* to
# https://esrf.net/* before this file is consulted, so we only need to
# redirect the www host. We list http:// explicitly as a defence in depth in
# case Always-HTTPS is ever disabled; both rules send traffic to the canonical
# https://esrf.net origin. Query strings are preserved automatically by
# Cloudflare for 301 responses; :splat preserves the path.
https://www.esrf.net/* https://esrf.net/:splat 301
http://www.esrf.net/*  https://esrf.net/:splat 301

